Share this...FacebookTwitterRoland Tichy‚Äôs site here reports that although car traffic in the German city of Stuttgart has decreased significantly due to COVID-19, the drop in NO2 content has only been ‚Äúslight‚Äù.
 So it cannot be the evil diesel engine cars that are ‚Äúchoking‚Äù our cities.

Image: NASA here (public domain)¬†
‚ÄúThe Corona crisis is bringing it to light: car traffic has decreased significantly, but the air quality in city centers has hardly changed,‚Äù Tichy comments.
Environmental claim exposed as false
Recall that a major reduction of diesel engines was supposed to improve air quality. After all, experts at the Baden-W√ºrttemberg State Institute for the Environment (LUBW), for example, have attributed a large 80 percent share of air pollutants especially to diesel vehicles ‚Äì so they have to be banned soon.
Yet Tichy notes: ‚ÄúIf this is true, the ‚Äòshutdown‚Äô would have to have a drastic effect. But it does not.‚Äù
It turns out that the involuntary ‚Äúcorona experiment‚Äù with its widespread stop of car traffic has exposed bare the false claim made by environmental activists: Diesel cars are responsible for polluting the air of German cities.


