Diesel car bans ‚Äúpointless‚Äù
According to Tichy, the ‚ÄúCorona Experiment‚Äù exposes just how pointless driving bans issued by the green transport ministers can be. ‚ÄúThey obviously have no effect on the NO2 concentrations in the air.‚Äù
‚ÄúThe measured values, for example, at the Am Neckartor station in the Stuttgart city center were already below the limit value of 40 ¬µg/m3 in February and March, ‚Äù writes Tichy. ‚ÄúAt that time, traffic was still flowing and ‚Äòshutdown‚Äô had not yet been announced.‚Äù
Other larger factors
Tichy adds that engineer and measurement expert Martin Schraag accuses proponents of car bans of data ‚Äúmanipulation‚Äù and reminds that today‚Äôs ‚Äúnewer vehicles and those retrofitted with software updates hardly emit any exhaust gases. This should also have been reflected in the results.‚Äù
Schraag notes that NO2 values fluctuate strongly and depend heavily on Stuttgart‚Äôs weather conditions and wintertime¬† heating can be the cause.
‚ÄúThe weather, if you look at the data, has a decisive influence,‚Äù Tichy comments. ‚ÄúThe experts of the LUBW environment office obviously did not care about these influences and officially know nothing about them. They still assume that traffic accounts for 80 percent of air pollutants.‚Äù
At a loss for words
Now they are facing difficulties in explaining the situation. As Schraag suspects, the 80 percent figure cannot be correct if there are significantly fewer cars on the road and yet the values have not changed.
The Bavarian State Office for the Environment also confirmed that the air pollutants in the city of W√ºrzburg ‚Äì hometown of former NBA superstar Dirk Nowitzski ‚Äì had hardly changed either although traffic has decreased significantly.


