Flaming space debris ‚Äî the remains of a Russian satellite ‚Äî came hurtling
back to Earth not far from a passenger jet on its way to Auckland, New Zealand.
Here‚Äôs further proof for the growing concern of the  increasing amounts of space junk orbiting our planet. From the article: ‚ÄòThe pilot of a Lan Chile Airbus A340 ‚Ä¶ notified air traffic controllers at Auckland Oceanic Center after seeing flaming space junk hurtling across the sky just five nautical miles in front of and behind his plane‚Ä¶‚Äô
Yikes!


