and Pierre Gosselin
It‚Äôs been a particularly mild winter in Europe this year. But that hasn‚Äôt changed the long-term trend over the past 30 years.
Now that the February 2020 data have been coming in, we plot the mean February temperatures for some countries in Europe.
Sweden
Three of 5 stations show February mean temperature in Greta Thunberg‚Äôs Sweden have had a cooling trend since 1988! The real data will probably make the climate alarmists upset.

Data source: JMA.¬†
Great Britain
Twelve of 14 stations in UK show February mean temperatures have had a cooling or no warming trend since 1992! (Note: those 14 stations have data dating back at least to 1980s):

Source: JMA
Finland


