A portion of Dr. Stallinga‚Äôs paper worth highlighting ‚Äì which he mentions only in passing ‚Äì refers to the early history of the Earth‚Äôs greenhouse effect paradigm.
K. √Öngstr√∂m receives little attention as a pioneer of the conceptualization that warming and cooling resul from radiative imbalances within a planetary greenhouse effect.
About 120 years ago, √Öngstr√∂m (1900) contradicted the oft-cited Arrhenius (1896) ‚Äì the atmospheric physicist referred to by proponents of anthropogenic global warming.
√Öngstr√∂m suggested Earth‚Äôs greenhouse effect is already saturated in its current (1900) state, and therefore increasing CO2 will have ‚Äúno effect whatsoever‚Äù on climate (Stallinga, 2020).
√Öngstr√∂m‚Äôs conclusions were largely ignored.

