Share this...FacebookTwitterBy Kirye 
and Pierre Gosselin
So what‚Äôs going on?
NASA and other government agencies keep telling us that the globe is warming and ice becoming more rare, yet when look out the window, things often appear to be going the opposite direction.
Rare cold, snow grip Greece
For example, the¬†Greek Reporter here¬†informed how a ‚Äúrare spring snow‚Äù blanketed large parts of northern Greece. It reported: ‚ÄúOf course, Northern Greece is used to low temperatures and snow, but even for their standards, such an intense snowfall in April is rare.‚Äù
Moreover, the widely read Electroverse weather site here reported how southeast Europe had seen its ‚Äúcoldest April morning in a decade‚Äù, potentially causing widespread crop damage.
So why are such events happening when they aren‚Äôt supposed to be?
Altering: from cooling to warming
Today we look at the NASA data from two stations in Greece: Makedonia and Larissa, shown below:



<!--
