Share this...FacebookTwitterLast Thursday evening in M√ºnster, Germany, amid an atmosphere of loudly protesting students and Extinction Rebellion activists outside shouting obscenities and beating drums, prominent SPD social democrat and climate science critic Prof. Fritz Vahrenholt spoke on why Germany was headed down the wrong path with its now flailing transition to green energies, dubbed ‚ÄúEnergiewende‚Äú.

Prof. Fritz Vahrenholt. Image: GWPF.¬†
Vahrenholt called the Energiewende: ‚ÄúAn impending disaster.‚Äù
According to the Westf√§lische Nachricten here, ‚ÄúScientists for Future activists handed out leaflets to emphasize that in their opinion the climate models of the IPCC (‚ÄòIntergovernmental Panel on Climate Change‚Äô) accurately depicted climate warming and that only trace gas CO2 was responsible for it.‚Äù
